  "text": "To alleviate the sparsity of supervision caused by rare positive examples (P3), we also consider the AP loss across all the classes. More specifically, we treat the matrices y(c) and y * (c) as concatenated vectors y and y * , respectively, and set L AP C = L AP (y, y * ). (23) This practice is consistent with [CITATION_1] .",
